Former governor of Borno State, Senator Ali Modu Sheriff has formally withdrawn from the national chairmanship race of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC).   DSS raises the alarm over planned violence in North Central     Electoral Act: NASS seeks legal advice, may challenge court…     Last Man Standing: Sanwo-Olu, Abiodun, Akande watch Lateef…   Sheriff made this declaration on Sunday in Abuja. The frontline politician said he made the decision after the party zoned the office of the national chairman to the North Central region as he is from the North East region.